I've got lots of goodies for your listening pleasure this episode, some old but much more are new. I've also got plenty of Chicago talent for you; starting out with one of Herbie Hancock's earlier works which has been sampled by many, as well as entries from duo Monologic and a track from the forthcoming album, "Year of the Rebel" from producer Anthony Nicholson. Any 4hero fans are also going to recognize the broken beat sounds of Dego who has a brand new solo album. Please support artistry in music, check the tracklisting, and buy anything that catches your ear! Tracklisting:
